sbml2modelica.utils

Class Log

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.utils.Log

  • public class Log
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a set of methods which allows logging operations.
    Using this class it is possible to write four kinds of log message to the log file
    • Regular message: This kind of message writes in the log file a message with its timestamp.
    • Warning: This kind of message writes in the log file a regular message labeled as a warning.
    • Error: This kind of message writes in the log file a regular message labeled as an error.
    • Fatal Error: This kind of message writes in the log file a regular message labeled as a fatal error.
    Author:
    Filippo Maggioli

    • Method Detail

      • initLogFile

        private static void initLogFile()
        This method initializes the log file.
        The initialization consists in creating the File object representing the file and then associating to it a BufferedWriter object.
        If no filename for the log file is provided, then default is assumed.

      • FatalError

        public static void FatalError(java.lang.String msg,
                              int errcode)
        This method writes to the log file a fatal error message, labaled with the current timestamp. Then, it terminate the application with the given exit code.
        Parameters:
        msg - The fatal error to write.
        errcode - The exit code with which the application must be terminated.

      • setLogFile

        public static boolean setLogFile(java.lang.String filename)
        This method sets the current log file to the file pointed by the given filename and returns a boolean value identifying if the operation has been completed correctly.
        WARNING: This method should be called before the log file is initialized, otherwise the Log class will continue to operate on the previous file, but the eventual error feedback given by the class will refer to the newer one.
        Parameters:
        filename - The new log file.
        Returns:
        true if the operation is completed successfully, false otherwise.

      • setVerbosity

        public static boolean setVerbosity(int verbosity)
        This method sets the current verbosity of the logger to the given value and returns a boolean value which informs the caller about the success of the operation.
        The admissible values for the verbosity are 0, 1, 2 and 3. If the given value is smaller than 0, the verbosity is set to 0 and the method returns false. If the given value is greater than 3, the verbosity is set to 3 and the methos returns false. Otherwise, the verbosity is set to the given value and the method returns true.
        Parameters:
        verbosity - The verbosity value to set.
        Returns:
        true if the given value is valid, false otherwise.
